@startuml
<style>
element {MinimumWidth 200}
</style>

title Firmware Main Loop (20 ms Tick-Based, Non-Blocking)

start

:Initialize hardware;

repeat

:Wait 20 ms;

:Process button input;
note right
Detect press–release event.
If pump is not currently running:
  - Increase selected watering duration.
  - Schedule display update pulse.
end note

:Process display pulse;
note right
If a pulse is scheduled:
  - Drive display clock HIGH for one tick.
On the next tick:
  - Drive display clock LOW.
The display hardware handles digit increment and wrapping.
end note

:Update internal time counters;

if (One second elapsed?) then (yes)

    :Update pump runtime state;
    note right
    If watering is active:
      - Keep pump enabled.
      - Decrease remaining time of current 5-second segment.
      - When the segment completes:
          - Decrease number of remaining segments.
          - If segments remain, start next 5-second segment.
    If no watering is active:
      - Ensure pump is disabled.
    end note

    if (One hour elapsed?) then (yes)

        :Evaluate soil moisture;

        if (Soil is dry?) then (yes)
            :Start watering cycle using selected duration;
            note right
            This updates internal runtime state only.
            The pump output will be enabled during the
            next periodic pump update.
            No blocking operation occurs here.
            end note
        else (no)
        endif

    else (no)
    endif

else (no)
endif

repeat while (true)
@enduml